## Context

- All 5 phases of WRN-MSI Pan-Cancer Dependency Atlas now complete
- Phase 1: Tiered MSI classifier → 70 MSI-H lines, 2 qualifying types (Bowel, Uterus)
- Phase 2: WRN ROBUST SL in Bowel (d=-2.844) and Uterus (d=-1.086). TP53-GOF hotspots reduce WRN dependency (resistance biomarker)
- Phase 3: 186 gained / 98 lost dependencies. Novel: PELO (d=-2.876), RPL22L1 (d=-2.602), DHX9 (d=-1.682)
- Phase 4: AZD-7648 (DNA-PK inh) MSI-H selective (d=-0.526, FDR=0.018). WRN inhibitors not in PRISM.
- Phase 5: ~61,854 US MSI-H patients/yr. COADREAD top priority (score=28.6). 13 tumor types lack WRN trial enrollment. PAAD lowest pembro ORR (18%) — strongest WRN inhibitor combination case.
- All code in src/wrn_msi_pancancer_atlas/, outputs in output/wrn-msi-pancancer-atlas/
- No remaining developer tasks for this project — atlas ready for analyst validation
